<div class="pocket-item"><a href="https://owl.english.purdue.edu/owl/resource/540/01/" target="_blank"><span>How to Use Articles (a/an/the)</span><p>This handout discusses the differences between indefinite articles (a/an) and definite articles (the).What is an article? Basically, an article is an adjective. Like adjectives, articles modify nouns.</p><p class="pocket-tags"><span>ery</span><span>sdfg</span><span>test</span></p></a><input name="tags" type="text" placeholder="Custom Tags" data-role="tagsinput"value="123"data-content-id="1188529" data-provider="pocket"/></div><div class="pocket-item"><a href="http://esl.fis.edu/grammar/rules/article.htm" target="_blank"><span>Articles</span><p>The 3 articles in English are a, an and the. The learner has to decide noun-by-noun which one of the articles to use*. In fact, there are 4 choices to make, because sometimes no article is necessary. Native-speakers, of course, use the articles correctly without thinking in everyday spoken language.</p></a><input name="tags" type="text" placeholder="Custom Tags" data-role="tagsinput"value="qwe"data-content-id="4818785" data-provider="pocket"/></div>